                  </hi>. I am a watch-maker, and live in Bear-street, Lincoln's-inn-fields. On the 1st of December I was in Benjamin-street, St. Se<lb></lb>pulchre's, and felt a slight tug at my pocket—I felt and missed my hand<lb></lb>kerchief—I turned and saw the prisoner nearest to me—he walked away—I walked after him, and he turned and saw me, and ran—I ran and took him—he asked what I took him for—I said, "For taking my handkerchief"—he denied it, but at the same time he had it in his hand, and was endea<lb></lb>vouring</p>
